172
00:09:00,810 --> 00:09:03,730
Ow, ow, ow!

173
00:09:05,550 --> 00:09:08,480
Go back! Go back! Rotate 180 degrees!

174
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:29,210
What the hell is this?!

175
00:09:32,170 --> 00:09:34,800
Wh-Wh-What in the world
is this hulking piece of iron?!

176
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,260
A ship?

177
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:39,600
Impossible! Something shaped
like this isn't seaworthy!

178
00:09:43,220 --> 00:09:45,600
Hey, frog! Run! What're you doing?!

179
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:56,900
Ah! It got run over!

180
00:10:21,260 --> 00:10:23,560
The ship was puffing out smoke!

181
00:10:34,380 --> 00:10:35,610
Pirates...?

182
00:10:35,610 --> 00:10:38,360
Grandma! Grandma! Pirates are here!

183
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:41,740
What?! Is that so, Chimney?!

184
00:10:41,740 --> 00:10:45,280
Okay then, bring the transponder snail to me!

185
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:46,000
Okay!

186
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:50,120
This is a problem.
Someone came out of the building.

187
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:52,080
They're gonna call for help.

188
00:10:53,250 --> 00:10:54,690
Here it is, Grandma!

189
00:10:54,690 --> 00:10:56,550
Um... Hello?

190
00:10:56,550 --> 00:11:01,210
Let's see... What was it? I forgot.

191
00:11:01,210 --> 00:11:02,510
She's wasted?!

192
00:11:07,470 --> 00:11:13,080
Oh? Paille, huh? It goes good with booze.

193
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:15,440
Whoa! This is tasty!

194
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:19,200
I'm Chimney. This is our cat, Gonbe,

195
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,690
and Grandma Kokoro.

196
00:11:20,690 --> 00:11:24,830
You guys aren't train robbers, are you?

197
00:11:24,830 --> 00:11:27,700
I'm Luffy. I'm the man
who'll be King of the Pirates.

198
00:11:27,700 --> 00:11:28,420
Really?!

199
00:11:28,420 --> 00:11:29,000
Yeah.

200
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,960
What a funny guy.

201
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:34,790
Say, Chimney, that thing
is a steamship, right?

202
00:11:34,790 --> 00:11:39,030
But with a shape like that,
there's no way it could ever sail.

203
00:11:39,030 --> 00:11:41,170
Never seen nothin' like it, huh?

204
00:11:41,170 --> 00:11:43,720
This is the only place in the world it exists.

205
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:47,160
It's a sea train called the Puffing Tom.

206
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:48,680
Puffing Tom?

207
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:52,190
A steam engine turns the paddle wheels
as it rides the sea railway.

208
00:11:55,610 --> 00:11:56,790
Railway?

209
00:11:56,790 --> 00:12:00,190
That's right. It floats
just below the water's surface.

210
00:12:00,190 --> 00:12:05,190
The train travels the same route every day,
taking passengers from one island to another.

211
00:12:05,190 --> 00:12:07,120
It also hauls ships and delivers mail.

212
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:09,660
She's right. There really is a railway.

213
00:12:09,660 --> 00:12:12,500
Yup! There's both a signal and a partition.

214
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:14,330
It's dangerous to cross the barrier!

215
00:12:14,330 --> 00:12:18,390
Dangerous or not,
that guy wouldn't understand, right?

216
00:12:18,390 --> 00:12:22,090
It wasn't nice to send him flying.
We were chasing him, you know.

217
00:12:22,090 --> 00:12:24,890
By "that guy," do you mean Yokozuna?

218
00:12:24,890 --> 00:12:26,990
Yep, that front-crawl frog.

219
00:12:26,990 --> 00:12:29,900
Yokozuna wouldn't die from that.

220
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:33,090
He's the source of all our
headaches here at Shift Station.

221
00:12:33,090 --> 00:12:36,700
He loves testing his strength
by trying to defeat the sea train.

222
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:38,180
He'll be back.

223
00:12:38,180 --> 00:12:42,120
Testing his strength? Oh!
That's why he stood his ground, huh?

224
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:43,720
He's sure got guts.

225
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:46,370
Give me a break! He's a royal pain!

226
00:12:46,370 --> 00:12:49,450
The grill also keeps getting broken!

227
00:12:49,450 --> 00:12:53,910
Every time he shows up,
the passengers freak out!

228
00:12:53,910 --> 00:12:55,800
So that's what he's doing...

229
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:57,710
Okay, then! I won't eat him!

230
00:12:57,710 --> 00:12:59,440
I can't eat a fighter!

231
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:01,800
Wanting to eat him was your first mistake!

232
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:05,800
So, you guys headed somewhere?

233
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:09,010
If you're gonna take
the sea train from here, there's:

234
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:16,140
St. Poplar, Town of the Spring Queen...
Pucci, the Gourmet Town...

235
00:13:16,140 --> 00:13:18,860
and San Faldo, the Carnival Town!

236
00:13:18,860 --> 00:13:20,900
They're all fun places.

237
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:25,820
If you work for the government,
you'd take a separate, special train.

238
00:13:25,820 --> 00:13:27,460
Okay, we'll pick the Gourmet Town.

239
00:13:27,460 --> 00:13:28,700
No, we won't!

240
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:32,500
Since we've got our own ship,
we won't need the train.

241
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:33,700
We can follow our log.

242
00:13:33,700 --> 00:13:35,750
Oh? Where's it pointing?

243
00:13:35,750 --> 00:13:37,540
Due east from here.

244
00:13:37,540 --> 00:13:41,460
So I see... That would be
none other than Water Seven.

245
00:13:41,460 --> 00:13:45,470
The train you saw earlier came
from that island's Blue Station.

246
00:13:46,430 --> 00:13:49,140
It's called the City of Water.
It's a real nice place.

247
00:13:49,140 --> 00:13:53,150
What's more, the city is known far and wide
for its shipbuilding industry.

248
00:13:53,150 --> 00:13:55,110
Their tech is the best in the world!

249
00:13:55,110 --> 00:14:00,000
Even the World Government favors
the ships built there! Amazing, right?

