00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:03,090
Then... they've got some
awesome shipwrights, right?!

251
00:14:03,090 --> 00:14:09,490
Not just "some"! Only the world's
best shipwrights hang out there!

252
00:14:09,490 --> 00:14:10,540
Usopp!

253
00:14:10,540 --> 00:14:11,800
Yeah!

254
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:13,600
Alright! I've decided!

255
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:16,370
We'll go and get a shipwright
to join us for sure!

256
00:14:16,370 --> 00:14:20,360
Oh, is that right? Then hold on a sec.

257
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:22,090
Up I go!

258
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:25,170
What's she up to?

259
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:25,170
Beats me.

260
00:14:25,170 --> 00:14:30,290
Well, then... Here's a basic map
of the island and a letter of introduction.

261
00:14:30,290 --> 00:14:35,600
Hand this to a guy named Iceburg
and ask him to fix up your ship real good.

262
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:38,940
Water Seven is a big place. Don't get lost.

263
00:14:38,940 --> 00:14:40,130
Whoa!

264
00:14:40,130 --> 00:14:42,900
You have a heart of gold,
Miss Kokoro! You're so kind!

265
00:14:47,390 --> 00:14:50,910
In a bit, we're gonna go back
to Water Seven too.

266
00:14:50,910 --> 00:14:56,810
Oh, true! If we meet again,
first round's on me at my favorite bar.

267
00:14:57,580 --> 00:15:00,170
Okay! I hope we see you guys again!

268
00:15:00,170 --> 00:15:05,090
At Water Seven, it'll take about a week
for the log to register, so kick back and relax.

269
00:15:06,260 --> 00:15:08,510
Yeah! Thanks!

270
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:13,400
All right, guys! Get ready to set sail!

271
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,180
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

272
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:15,200
Well then, we're off!

273
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:18,560
Thanks for all your help,
Miss Kokoro and Chimney!

274
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,650
Be careful!

275
00:15:28,820 --> 00:15:32,030
Watch out for the government people!

276
00:15:32,030 --> 00:15:34,950
Yahoo! Let's go!

277
00:15:34,950 --> 00:15:37,620
To the city of meat! Yahoo!

278
00:15:37,620 --> 00:15:39,580
Were you even listening?

279
00:15:49,040 --> 00:15:51,690
Mmm. What a nice breeze!

280
00:15:51,690 --> 00:15:54,500
Maybe we'll reach the City of Water
sooner than expected.

281
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,850
I hope so.

282
00:15:56,310 --> 00:16:01,260
Luffy, leave scouting out the shipwright to me.
I'll find us an incredibly gorgeous woman.

283
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:03,210
Don't be dumb! We need a shipwright!

284
00:16:03,210 --> 00:16:06,900
It's gotta be a big guy
the size of a mountain! Five meters tall!

285
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:11,490
But if he's too big,
he might not fit on this ship.

286
00:16:11,490 --> 00:16:14,090
All that matters is that he's skilled, right?

287
00:16:14,090 --> 00:16:18,490
The real question is if there's someone
crazy enough to want to be on a pirate ship.

288
00:16:18,490 --> 00:16:22,330
I can't wait! We're gonna make a new friend!

289
00:16:22,330 --> 00:16:26,340
We were lucky to stop at the station first
since they drew a map for us.

290
00:16:26,340 --> 00:16:30,170
If we go to the place on the map
and find that Iceburg guy...

291
00:16:31,470 --> 00:16:32,380
Oh, okay.

292
00:16:32,380 --> 00:16:34,260
This tells me nothing!

293
00:16:35,010 --> 00:16:36,510
Whoa! This is like Luffy's art.

294
00:16:36,510 --> 00:16:39,720
Here. We need to keep
an eye out for a guy like this.

295
00:16:40,350 --> 00:16:42,090
I'd run if I saw a guy like that.

296
00:16:42,090 --> 00:16:45,680
Same here. I'd hop on the next ship
and hightail it out to sea.

297
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:49,410
But a thug like this might chase me
into open water like an octopus.

298
00:16:49,410 --> 00:16:51,240
What are you guys jabbering about?

299
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:52,700
Come here, guys!

300
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:55,870
I'll give you an allowance
for the week we're ashore.

301
00:16:55,870 --> 00:16:57,520
Seriously?! Yay! I'm first!

302
00:16:57,520 --> 00:16:59,240
Whoa! That's generous!

303
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,750
Hey! Get in line!

304
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:05,710
– Allowance! Allowance! Allowance!
– Allowance! Allowance! Allowance!

305
00:17:15,780 --> 00:17:17,600
You doing okay, Usopp?

306
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:22,890
This tinplate patchwork brings back
memories of battles and adventure.

307
00:17:22,890 --> 00:17:27,810
I can't help but gush over
the thought of her upcoming repairs.

308
00:17:27,810 --> 00:17:29,650
I get it, but...

309
00:17:29,270 --> 00:17:29,650
Huh?

310
00:17:29,650 --> 00:17:34,860
our journey—especially since we entered
the Grand Line—has taken quite a toll on the Merry.

311
00:17:34,860 --> 00:17:38,410
The deck creaks, and the ship's
bottom is pretty leaky.

312
00:17:38,410 --> 00:17:41,950
If nothing's done, that'll be it
for both the ship and us.

313
00:17:41,950 --> 00:17:44,950
Yeah, but we're filthy rich now.

314
00:17:44,950 --> 00:17:48,500
We can make her good as new!
And more powerful, too!

315
00:17:49,260 --> 00:17:50,900
Yeah! More cannons!

316
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:52,580
Also, a bronze statue!

317
00:17:53,260 --> 00:17:54,890
Hey, is that it?

318
00:17:54,890 --> 00:17:55,760
– Huh?
– Huh?

319
00:17:57,930 --> 00:18:01,740
It's the island! We can see the island!

320
00:18:02,810 --> 00:18:05,090
Okay, guys! Row!

321
00:18:05,090 --> 00:18:08,020
We've got a decent tailwind.
We shouldn't waste energy!

322
00:18:18,280 --> 00:18:19,410
How wonderful!

323
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:22,740
It's incredible!

324
00:18:28,010 --> 00:18:30,370
What is this place?!

325
00:18:39,590 --> 00:18:41,800
The fountain's enormous!

326
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:45,720
Unbelievable! An actual industrial city!

327
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:47,430
That's why it has the sea train.

328
00:18:47,430 --> 00:18:49,600
That must be the station in front.

329
00:18:50,410 --> 00:18:52,600
It says "Blue Station."

330
00:18:54,130 --> 00:18:55,610
I wonder where we dock.

331
00:18:55,610 --> 00:18:56,940
In town somewhere?

332
00:18:57,690 --> 00:19:00,200
Hey, you there!

333
00:18:59,610 --> 00:19:00,200
Hm?

334
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:03,600
Pirates shouldn't openly sail out in front.

335
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:05,790
Go around to the Backstreets!

336
00:19:06,810 --> 00:19:09,250
Okay! Thanks!

337
00:19:14,750 --> 00:19:17,710
Whoa, this is amazing! A city on the water?!

338
00:19:17,710 --> 00:19:21,590
Wow! This place is cool! Such a pretty city!

339
00:19:29,940 --> 00:19:34,940
But the city is flooded.
The houses are submerged in the sea.

340
00:19:34,940 --> 00:19:36,270
Look again.

341
00:19:36,270 --> 00:19:39,860
The city was designed
with its base underwater.

342
00:19:39,860 --> 00:19:42,320
You can see the foundation underneath.

343
00:19:43,090 --> 00:19:45,530
Oh, true! The pillars raise the structures!

344
00:19:45,530 --> 00:19:48,160
I see... That's why it's called
the City of Water, huh?

345
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:51,120
Hey, hurry up and dock the ship!

346
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:57,920
Hey, listen up, you guys!
Pirate ships should steer clear of this area!

347
00:19:57,920 --> 00:20:00,450
Did you come here to plunder?

348
00:20:00,450 --> 00:20:03,080
No! We wanna get our ship repaired!

349
00:20:03,080 --> 00:20:05,390
People just up and ask
if we're gonna plunder...?

350
00:20:05,390 --> 00:20:10,380
In that case, there's a cape just ahead,
so anchor your ship there for now!

351
00:20:10,380 --> 00:20:11,980
Okay!

352
00:20:11,980 --> 00:20:13,500
Thanks!

353
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:14,810
Again?

354
00:20:14,810 --> 00:20:17,520
What'd you expect? We're pirates, after all.

355
00:20:19,540 --> 00:20:21,600
This spot's okay, right?

356
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:25,210
It sure is bleak though.

357
00:20:25,210 --> 00:20:27,770
All right, then! Furl the sail!

358
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:36,750
What're you doing?!

359
00:20:36,750 --> 00:20:39,840
Nothing! All I did was pull the rope!

360
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:47,510
You're kidding me!
The Going Merry has gotten this rickety?

361
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:52,350
Anyway, why aren't the people
on this island scared of pirates?

362
00:20:52,350 --> 00:20:55,620
Pirates probably come here for ships too.

363
00:20:55,620 --> 00:20:58,110
Less talking! More fixing!

364
00:20:58,110 --> 00:21:03,340
Maybe they have sentries strong enough
to deal with pirates who cause a ruckus?

365
00:21:03,340 --> 00:21:06,780
They probably do,
considering the size of the city.

366
00:21:06,780 --> 00:21:10,360
Is that so?! Then what're we
gonna do? This is bad.

367
00:21:10,360 --> 00:21:12,790
Why would it be bad? We're customers.

368
00:21:12,790 --> 00:21:14,120
Y-You think so?

369
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:15,680
Okay, then! See you later!

370
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:17,730
Wait, Luffy and Usopp!

371
00:21:19,040 --> 00:21:21,390
You two, come with me.

372
00:21:21,390 --> 00:21:22,380
– Hm?
– Hm?

373
00:21:24,010 --> 00:21:25,100
Come with you where?

374
00:21:25,100 --> 00:21:29,970
First, we'll take Miss Kokoro's letter of introduction
and go find the man named Iceburg.

375
00:21:29,970 --> 00:21:33,700
We'll ask him to facilitate the ship's repair.

376
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:37,060
Then we have to find a place
where we can cash in our gold.

377
00:21:37,060 --> 00:21:42,570
If that's it, then okay!
Onward! To the City of Water!

378
00:21:42,570 --> 00:21:44,690
You're forgetting the gold.

379
00:21:44,690 --> 00:21:45,900
Ah...

380
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:50,360
Hey! Some pirates are
raising hell at Dock One!

381
00:21:50,360 --> 00:21:51,870
What?! For real?!

382
00:21:51,870 --> 00:21:54,580
We'd better hurry and see!

383
00:21:55,540 --> 00:21:58,070
I don't understand what you're talking about.

384
00:21:58,070 --> 00:22:00,230
Well, actually...

385
00:22:03,510 --> 00:22:06,200
I thought about it carefully.

386
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:09,310
I thought about it really carefully.

387
00:22:09,310 --> 00:22:12,300
While it's true that you guys repaired our ship,

388
00:22:12,300 --> 00:22:16,960
I couldn't help but notice
the invoice was a bit too high.

389
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:20,360
You're interrupting our work.

390
00:22:20,360 --> 00:22:25,060
So... I decided not to pay—not one belly.

391
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:29,500
Thanks for the flawless repairs!

392
00:22:31,240 --> 00:22:33,290
Plus, it's all free!

393
00:22:44,710 --> 00:22:47,600
Well, Kalifa, what's going on over there?

394
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:50,680
You see, Mr. Iceburg,
they're customers of Dock One.

395
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:53,490
The repairs are complete,
but they refuse to pay.

396
00:22:54,140 --> 00:22:56,000
That's sexual harassment.

397
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:59,560
Well... I suppose that is sexual harassment.

398
00:23:10,540 --> 00:23:14,240
Sir, you'd be wise not to
provoke craftsmen like that.

399
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:27,460
B-Boss!

400
00:23:27,460 --> 00:23:29,470
– Boss!
– Boss!

401
00:23:30,270 --> 00:23:31,430
Oh, pardon me.

402
00:23:31,430 --> 00:23:36,510
You son of a bitch!
You should watch where you're going!

403
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:40,440
Oh, pardon me.

404
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:45,400
Y-You bastards! Are you picking a fight?!
Just who do you think we are?!

405
00:23:55,160 --> 00:23:58,790
Hey, have you test-fired the cannon?

406
00:23:58,790 --> 00:24:00,540
Oh, not yet, sir.

407
00:24:03,460 --> 00:24:07,460
Dammit! Who the hell are you guys?!

408
00:24:07,910 --> 00:24:10,920
We'll remember this!

409
00:24:23,500 --> 00:24:25,500
The pirate way of doing things

410
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:28,860
doesn't work on craftsmen's turf, now, does it?

411
00:24:30,300 --> 00:24:32,610
Should we go to the exchange shop first?

412
00:24:32,610 --> 00:24:35,170
Why? Let's go to the shipyard.

413
00:24:35,170 --> 00:24:40,700
But we can't just walk around the island
with this much gold. It puts me on edge.

414
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:43,160
Isn't it worth the same after it's exchanged?

415
00:24:43,160 --> 00:24:46,830
Even so, the size of our load
might attract attention, don't you think?

416
00:24:46,830 --> 00:24:48,730
What if we run into no good thieves?

417
00:24:48,730 --> 00:24:50,380
But we're thieves too!

418
00:24:50,380 --> 00:24:54,720
He's got a point. Trading it in for bills
would mean we each hold on to some of it.

419
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:57,680
Hey, what's with that remark?

420
00:24:57,680 --> 00:25:00,000
Is there a problem
if I'm the one carrying it?

421
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:02,510
Yeah. You might drop it or lose it somewhere.

422
00:25:02,510 --> 00:25:04,730
Yeah, he would. It's Luffy after all.

423
00:25:04,730 --> 00:25:07,610
What?! Guys! Don't you trust me?!

424
00:25:07,610 --> 00:25:08,360
– Nope!
– Nope!

425
00:25:09,570 --> 00:25:13,530
That really hurts! I might not recover from thi–

426
00:25:13,530 --> 00:25:14,200
Hm?

427
00:25:14,900 --> 00:25:18,490
Is this the only entrance to the city?

428
00:25:19,490 --> 00:25:21,050
A rental bull shop?

429
00:25:21,050 --> 00:25:22,120
What's that?

430
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:24,000
What do they rent out?

431
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:24,040
What do they rent out?

432
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:24,090
What do they rent out?

433
00:25:24,090 --> 00:25:24,130
What do they rent out?

434
00:25:24,130 --> 00:25:24,170
What do they rent out?

435
00:25:24,170 --> 00:25:24,210
What do they rent out?

436
00:25:24,210 --> 00:25:24,250
What do they rent out?

437
00:25:24,250 --> 00:25:24,290
What do they rent out?

438
00:25:24,340 --> 00:25:25,380
What's a "bull"?

439
00:25:25,380 --> 00:25:25,420
What's a "bull"?

440
00:25:25,420 --> 00:25:25,460
What's a "bull"?

441
00:25:25,460 --> 00:25:25,500
What's a "bull"?

442
00:25:25,500 --> 00:25:25,550
What's a "bull"?

443
00:25:25,550 --> 00:25:25,590
What's a "bull"?

444
00:25:25,590 --> 00:25:25,630
What's a "bull"?

445
00:25:25,710 --> 00:25:27,840
Beats me. Bulldogs?

446
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:30,000
Can't be, right?

447
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:32,520
Excuse me! We'd like to rent some bulls!

448
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:34,220
Ask what they are first!

449
00:25:35,420 --> 00:25:38,390
Welcome! Here to rent bulls,
right? For how many?

450
00:25:38,390 --> 00:25:39,510
Three of us!

451
00:25:39,510 --> 00:25:41,500
What kind of bulls would you like?

452
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:44,180
There are three classes:
yagara, rabuka, and king.

453
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:47,320
Well, for the three of you,
two yagaras would probably do.

454
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:49,150
Okay, roast 'em nice and tasty!

455
00:25:49,150 --> 00:25:50,980
Don't say weird things, you weirdo!

456
00:25:51,700 --> 00:25:54,440
Oh? Your log pose led you here?

457
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:55,160
Yep.

458
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:57,390
That's quite the undertaking, you guys.

459
00:25:57,390 --> 00:25:59,700
Then you had no idea
what bulls were, did you?

460
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:00,750
– Right.
– Right.

461
00:26:00,750 --> 00:26:03,290
Well, long story short, those are bulls.

462
00:26:03,290 --> 00:26:05,960
Yagara bulls. You'll see them all over town.

463
00:26:05,960 --> 00:26:10,240
In this area, there's a fish called a yagara
that swims with its head out.

464
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:13,960
This is the City of Water.
There are more canals than walkways.

465
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:17,590
The residents here see bulls
as a necessary form of transportation.

466
00:26:18,300 --> 00:26:20,760
Same goes for any sightseeing on the island.

467
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:22,820
That fish is pulling a boat?

468
00:26:22,820 --> 00:26:25,430
Actually, they let people ride on their backs.

469
00:26:25,430 --> 00:26:29,650
Well, it's like horseback riding
or riding in a carriage on land.

470
00:26:29,650 --> 00:26:31,610
In we go!

471
00:26:31,610 --> 00:26:35,650
You see the fish pen there?
Well, try and ride on one. It's comfortable.

472
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:40,260
For a couple of two-passenger
yagara bulls, it'll be 2,000 belly, all told.

473
00:26:40,260 --> 00:26:41,740
Wow, they're cute!

474
00:26:41,740 --> 00:26:44,410
It's a fish that looks like a horse.

475
00:26:45,660 --> 00:26:49,500
You jerk! What'd you do that for?!

476
00:26:49,500 --> 00:26:52,840
Oh? He must like you.
Let's get that one for you.

477
00:26:59,180 --> 00:27:01,390
Can he carry heavy stuff okay?

478
00:27:01,390 --> 00:27:05,310
Their power is incredible! They're often used
when moving household goods.

479
00:27:05,950 --> 00:27:08,250
Quite the bag, huh? Whatcha got in there?

480
00:27:08,250 --> 00:27:09,350
Gold.

481
00:27:10,290 --> 00:27:13,230
Good one! Whatever it is, they can handle it.

482
00:27:13,230 --> 00:27:13,860
See?

483
00:27:13,860 --> 00:27:16,030
Whoa! Gimme!

484
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:16,040
No way!

485
00:27:16,040 --> 00:27:18,030
This guy's awfully honest.

486
00:27:18,030 --> 00:27:20,700
And you! Don't show it off
to others so casually!

487
00:27:20,700 --> 00:27:22,690
Why's that? It's no big deal.

488
00:27:22,690 --> 00:27:24,740
My... That was a surprise.

489
00:27:24,740 --> 00:27:28,720
Well, then... It'll be a million belly
for two yagara bulls.

490
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:30,580
Hey, the price went up, pops.

491
00:27:30,580 --> 00:27:33,330
Oh, right, are there any
exchange shops around here?

492
00:27:33,330 --> 00:27:40,400
Yeah, there are, but with that amount of gold,
the shops here probably won't have enough money.

493
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:42,890
You should go downtown on Shipyard Island.

494
00:27:42,890 --> 00:27:46,720
Downtown Shipyard Island? Where's that?

495
00:27:46,720 --> 00:27:50,000
In that direction. Take this with you.

496
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:51,270
A map?! Aha!

497
00:27:52,010 --> 00:27:53,440
This'll be helpful! Thanks!

498
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:56,380
Pops, is the shipyard that way, too?

499
00:27:56,380 --> 00:27:58,810
Yeah. The world's number one shipyard!

500
00:27:58,810 --> 00:28:02,950
Perfect! Once we get the money,
we'll be real close to the shipyard.

501
00:28:02,950 --> 00:28:06,740
Yeah. We can finally have
the Going Merry repaired!

